<paragraph id="085436FB127EFFCBFF84F9F6FC0C6C25" blockId="27.[113,1089,1580,1627]" pageId="27" pageNumber="684">
<emphasis id="3A9FEAE9127EFFCBFF84F9F6FDE76C41" bold="true" box="[113,586,1580,1600]" pageId="27" pageNumber="684">
Specimen studied. 
<collectingCountry id="70FC766B127EFFCBFEEBF9F6FE746C3F" box="[286,473,1580,1600]" name="French Guiana" pageId="27" pageNumber="684">FRENCH GUIANA</collectingCountry>
: COMMUNITE
</emphasis>
DE 
<emphasis id="3A9FEAE9127EFFCBFD98F9F7FD026C3F" bold="true" box="[621,687,1581,1600]" pageId="27" pageNumber="684">ROURA:</emphasis>
“Guyane Fr., 
<date id="7C55103B127EFFCBFCD9F9F6FC256C40" box="[812,904,1580,1599]" pageId="27" pageNumber="684" value="2010-04-12">12.iv.2010</date>
, Mont. des Chevaux, Comm. de Roura, RN2 PK22, 75 m, 
<geoCoordinate id="6DDF503C127EFFCBFE46F99DFDA06C24" box="[435,525,1606,1627]" degrees="4" direction="north" minutes="44" orientation="latitude" pageId="27" pageNumber="684" precision="15" seconds="56" value="4.748889">4°44′56′′N</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="6DDF503C127EFFCBFDE6F99DFDD36C24" box="[531,638,1606,1627]" degrees="52" direction="west" minutes="26" orientation="longitude" pageId="27" pageNumber="684" precision="15" seconds="28" value="-52.441113">52°26′28′′W</geoCoordinate>
, P.-H. Dalens leg.” (1 J, NMPC).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="085436FB1279FFCCFF40FF01FE506B6B" blockId="28.[151,1127,219,499]" pageId="28" pageNumber="685">
The poorly preserved specimen without the abdomen except for the part of terminal ventrites with the aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="90D02A7E1279FFCCFE54FF21FE5C6B6B" box="[417,497,251,276]" captionStart="Figs 30–39" captionStartId="9.[113,150,1516,1535]" captionTargetBox="[148,1042,221,1489]" captionTargetId="figure-11@9.[135,1064,212,1496]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 30–39.Aedeagi. 30 – Agrilaxia tristis Cobos, 1972; 31 – A. elegans sp. nov.; 32 – A. cordicollis sp. nov.; 33 – A. sulcifrons sp. nov.; 34 – A. convexifrons sp. nov.; 35 – A. caudata sp. nov.; 36 – A. prolonga sp. nov.; 37 – A. guianensis sp. nov.; 38 – A. sp. A; 39 – A. sp. B. Not to same scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5740770" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5740770/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="685">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="085436FB1279FFCCFF40FEC1FC856B0C" blockId="28.[151,1127,219,499]" pageId="28" pageNumber="685">
Small (
<quantity id="CF139B1E1279FFCCFEF7FEC6FEF56B4B" box="[258,344,284,308]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9" pageId="28" pageNumber="685" unit="mm" value="4.9">4.9 mm</quantity>
), completely black, slender (
<quantity id="CF139B1E1279FFCCFD7FFEC6FD4D6B4B" box="[650,736,284,308]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="28" pageNumber="685" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.1 mm</quantity>
), matt species with dark green frons, scutellum and lateral pronotal margins; very narrow, medial, pronotal stripe dark blue-green (
<figureCitation id="90D02A7E1279FFCCFF6AFE81FF436B0C" box="[159,238,347,371]" captionStart="Figs 9–16" captionStartId="5.[808,848,1224,1243]" captionTargetBox="[118,1088,232,1591]" captionTargetId="figure-11@5.[113,1090,219,1584]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 9–16. Agrilaxia, dorsal aspect. 9 – A. purpureiventris sp. nov., holotype ♀, 6.0 mm; 10 – A. convexifrons sp. nov., holotype ♀, 5.5 mm; 11 – A. caudata sp. nov., holotype J, 6.1 mm; 12 – A. prolonga sp. nov., holo- type J, 6.7 mm; 13 – A. gui- anensis sp. nov., holotype J, 5.7 mm; 14 – A. chrysifrons (Kerremans, 1896), J (Route de Kaw), 5.0 mm; 15 – A. sp. A, J (Roura), 4.8 mm; 16 – A. sp. B, J (Roura), 4.9 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5740766" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5740766/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="685">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
); preserved part of ventral side lustrous, dark bronze.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="085436FB1279FFCCFF40FEA1FCB26B8C" blockId="28.[151,1127,219,499]" pageId="28" pageNumber="685">
This species belongs most probably to the 
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D781279FFCCFD64FEA7FCEF6BEB" baseAuthorityName="Kerremans" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[657,834,381,404]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="685" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="opima">
<emphasis id="3A9FEAE91279FFCCFD64FEA7FCEF6BEB" box="[657,834,381,404]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="685">Agrilaxia opima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group (see above) which is characterised by the convex frons, deeply emarginate lateral pronotal margins and well defined “agriloid” and posthumeral carinae. Unfortunately this very badly preserved specimen is not suitable for the description of a new species.
</paragraph>
